Alternative approach: find the position of 2026 in the spiral sequence.

The spiral is built by adding numbers in a certain order, always placing the next number adjacent to the previous one in the spiral.

The sequence starts at 1, then goes around in layers.

The number of numbers up to layer n is 1 + 6*(1 + 2 + ... + n) = 1 + 3n(n+1).

We have 2026 is between layer 25 (1951) and layer 26 (2107), so it's in layer 26, starting at 1952.

The order in layer n is: start at the top (T) of the ring, then go clockwise: T, TR, R, BR, B, BL.

The first number in layer n is S(n-1) + 1.

The position within the layer is (number - S(n-1) - 1).

For 2026: S(25) = 1951, so position is 2026 - 1951 - 1 = 75.

So, 2026 is the 75th number in layer 26.

Now, in layer n, the numbers are placed in order: 1st is T, 2nd is TR, ..., 6th is BL, then next is T of next layer.

So, position 1: T, 2: TR, 3: R, 4: BR, 5: B, 6: BL, then next is T of next layer.

So position 75 mod 6 = 3 (since 75 / 6 = 12 with remainder 3), so it's the 3rd in the sequence: R.

So 2026 is at position R in layer 26.

